# SSH Hardening Auditor

Scan SSH server configurations against security best practices and CIS benchmarks. Reports findings with severity levels and actionable remediation steps.

## Quick Start

```bash
cd ssh-auditor
./venv/bin/pip install -e ".[dev]"

# Scan local sshd_config
./venv/bin/ssh-auditor scan /etc/ssh/sshd_config

# Scan a specific file
./venv/bin/ssh-auditor scan /path/to/sshd_config --format json

# List available rules
./venv/bin/ssh-auditor rules list
```

## Features

- Parses `sshd_config` including `Include`, `Match` blocks, and comments
- 30+ security checks against CIS SSH benchmarks
- Severity classification: critical, high, medium, low
- Colored terminal output with Rich
- JSON and HTML report export
- Dry-run auto-remediation (Phase 2)

## Installation

```bash
python3 -m venv venv
./venv/bin/pip install -e ".[dev]"
```

## Testing

```bash
./venv/bin/pytest tests/ -v
```

## Project Structure

```
ssh-auditor/
├── ssh_auditor/
│   ├── cli.py              # CLI entry point
│   ├── parser.py           # SSH config file parser
│   ├── rules/              # Rule definitions by category
│   │   ├── base.py         # Rule base class & Finding dataclass
│   │   ├── auth.py         # Authentication rules
│   │   ├── crypto.py       # Cipher/KEX/hostkey rules
│   │   ├── access.py       # Root login, allow/deny rules
│   │   └── hardening.py    # General hardening rules
│   └── reporter/           # Report generators
├── tests/
│   ├── fixtures/           # Sample sshd_config files
│   └── test_*.py           # Unit and integration tests
├── pyproject.toml
└── README.md
```

